OL,3,CTata Steel fined #1.5m after worker
OL,4,Ccrushed to death at Port Talbot plant
OL,6,FReport by ITV Wales Swansea
OL,7,FCorrespondent Dean Thomas-Welch
OL,9,FTata Steel UK has been fined 1.5
OL,10,Fmillion pounds after a contract
OL,11,Fengineer working at its Port Talbot
OL,12,Fsteel plant was killed by machinery.
OL,14,FJustin Day, 44, from Llamsamlet in
OL,15,FSwansea, died at the plant on the 25th
OL,16,Fof September 2019 while working as a
OL,17,Fcontractor with Mii Engineering.
OL,19,FMr Day was found slumped in a hot
OL,20,Frunning channel after the incident, a
OL,21,Fprevious inquest into his death heard.
