OL,6,F"It's plain Mr Day was a family man
OL,7,Fwhose death has left many of them
OL,8,Fbereft, and they have lost someone so
OL,9,Fprecious. I say that because it's a
OL,10,Ffact but also recognising that no fine
OL,11,Fthat I propose today can alleviate the
OL,12,Fsuffering of those who have lost a
OL,13,Floved one. No fine I give today can
OL,14,Frestore life."
