OL,6,FHaving previously pleaded guilty to
OL,7,Fbreaches of S2(1) and S3(1) of the
OL,8,FHealth and Safety at Work Act etc
OL,9,F1974, the company was fined #1.5
OL,10,Fmillion and ordered to pay prosecution
OL,11,Fcosts of #26,318.67
OL,13,FGethyn Jones, an inspector for the
OL,14,FHealth and Safety Executive, said:
OL,15,F"Justin Day's death could so easily
OL,16,Fhave been prevented.
OL,18,F"A much-loved family man is not here
OL,19,Fbecause of failures in health and
OL,20,Fsafety basics.
